the neanderthal man is a 78-minute , 1953 american black-and-white science fiction film produced independently by aubrey wisberg and jack pollexfen , as global productions inc. , from their own original screenplay . it starred robert shayne , richard crane and joyce terry , was directed by e. a. dupont , and was originally distributed in the united states by united artists corp . beverly garland , in a supporting role , appears here in her first feature film .